HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 23
By Clemmons
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Joyce Anne Vise of
Nashville.
WHEREAS, we were greatly saddened to learn of the passing of Joyce Anne Vise of
Nashville; and
WHEREAS, Joyce Vise was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Vise dedicated her life of service to education and community in varied
roles throughout her storied career: first as a teacher and later as a communications and
community relations director for Metro Nashville Public Schools; she was also involved with
Family and Children's Services in Nashville; and
WHEREAS, the daughter and granddaughter of Holocaust survivors, Ms. Vise was
deeply tied to her Jewish faith and identity, and she was a prominent member of The Temple
and Jewish community in Nashville; and
WHEREAS, she contributed her time and talents to a number of organizations and
events, including the Temple congregation, Cumberland University in Lebanon, and the Swan
Ball gala benefitting Cheekwood Estate and Gardens, to name but a few; and
WHEREAS, her father, Harry Vise, after whom the Doris and Harry Vise University
Library at Cumberland University is named, was a member of the school's Board of Trust, and
Joyce Vise continued to support the school in numerous ways, as well as speaking at an
International Holocaust Remembrance Day event on campus in 2020; and
WHEREAS, she had a special connection with her beloved Bichon Fris√©, Sugar, her
canine companion for many of her events and outings; and
